track_notes: Nice parking area with portable restrooms. The hike brings you to a fire tower at the summit Which is open on certain days during the summer months.
Just another way to approach Beech Mountain summit. Nice little hike to the fire tower. Activated this summit from a discrete position to the south east of the tower.
track_title: Route up Beech Mountain from South end of Long Pond.

track_notes:
I prefer the South Ridge Trail over the West Ridge. It has a more gradual climb, for us old people.
The trail head is on the south side of the Long Pond parking area. After a steep climb for a couple of hundred yards, the trail levels out, and is very pleasant for the rest of the way, and well maintained.
track_title: Route to Beech Mountain via the South Ridge Trail
